    "category": "Docker & Kubernetes",
    "question": "What is Docker? Tell about Dockerfile",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>🐳 <strong>What is Docker? Tell about Dockerfile</strong></h3>\n  <p>Docker is a containerization platform that packages applications along with their dependencies so they run consistently across different environments.</p>\n  <p>Dockerfile</p>\n  <p>A Dockerfile is a text file containing instructions to build a Docker image.</p>\n  <p>Example:</p>\n  <p>FROM ubuntu:22.04</p>\n  <p>RUN apt update</p>\n  <p>COPY . /app</p>\n  <p>WORKDIR /app</p>\n  <p>RUN apt install -y python3</p>\n  <p>CMD [\"python3\",\"app.py\"]</p>\n  <p>Common instructions:</p>\n  <p>•\tFROM</p>\n  <p>•\tRUN</p>\n  <p>•\tCOPY</p>\n  <p>•\tADD</p>\n  <p>•\tWORKDIR</p>\n  <p>•\tENV</p>\n  <p>•\tEXPOSE</p>\n  <p>•\tCMD</p>\n  <p>•\tENTRYPOINT</p>\n</div>",
