    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>💻 <strong>What is a Self-hosted Agent?</strong></h3>\n  <p>“A self-hosted agent is an agent installed on our own server or VM to run pipelines.</p>\n  <p>We use self-hosted agents when:</p>\n  <p>•\tCustom tools are needed</p>\n  <p>•\tSpecific network access required</p>\n  <p>•\tSecurity restrictions exist</p>\n  <p>•\tLarge builds require dedicated resources</p>\n  <p>Benefits:</p>\n  <p>•\tFull control</p>\n  <p>•\tBetter customization</p>\n  <p>•\tFaster execution for large workloads</p>\n  <p>One-line Answer:</p>\n  <p>Self-hosted agents run pipelines on our own infrastructure with more control and customization.”</p>\n</div>",
