    "question": "What are stages, jobs, and tasks?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>💡 <strong>What are stages, jobs, and tasks?</strong></h3>\n  <p>“In Azure DevOps pipeline hierarchy:</p>\n  <p>Stage</p>\n  <p>Logical grouping like:</p>\n  <p>•\tBuild</p>\n  <p>•\tTest</p>\n  <p>•\tDeploy</p>\n  <p>Job</p>\n  <p>Runs on an agent.</p>\n  <p>Example:</p>\n  <p>•\tLinux job</p>\n  <p>•\tWindows job</p>\n  <p>Task</p>\n  <p>Individual execution step.</p>\n  <p>Examples:</p>\n  <p>•\tRun script</p>\n  <p>•\tInstall Terraform</p>\n  <p>•\tBuild Docker image</p>\n  <p>Hierarchy:</p>\n  <p>Stage → Job → Task</p>\n  <p>One-line Answer:</p>\n  <p>Stages organize workflows, jobs run on agents, and tasks perform individual actions.”</p>\n  <p>AZURE</p>\n</div>",
