    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>💡 <strong>How do you design highly available architecture?</strong></h3>\n  <p>“We use:</p>\n  <p>•\tAvailability Zones</p>\n  <p>•\tMultiple instances</p>\n  <p>•\tLoad Balancers</p>\n  <p>•\tAuto scaling</p>\n  <p>•\tBackup and disaster recovery</p>\n  <p>Goal:</p>\n  <p>Avoid single point of failure.</p>\n  <p>One-line Answer:</p>\n  <p>High availability is achieved using redundancy, load balancing, and failover mechanisms.”</p>\n</div>",
    "difficulty": "Medium",
    "source": "DevOps Real Scenario Q&A",
    "company": null
