    "question": "Which Linux commands do you use to check IP address and verify internet connectivity?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>💻 <strong>Which Linux commands do you use to check IP address and verify internet connectivity?</strong></h3>\n  <p>• Check IP Address:</p>\n  <p>• 'ip addr show' (or 'ip a') - The modern and preferred command.</p>\n  <p>• 'ifconfig' - The legacy command (may require net-tools package).</p>\n  <p>• Verify Internet Connectivity:</p>\n  <p>• 'ping 8.8.8.8' - Tests network reachability to Google's public DNS.</p>\n  <p>• 'curl -I https://www.google.com' - Tests DNS resolution and HTTP connectivity.</p>\n</div>",
