    "id": 237,
    "category": "CI/CD & Pipelines",
    "question": "What is a Service Connection in Azure DevOps pipelines?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>☁️ <strong>What is a Service Connection in Azure DevOps pipelines?</strong></h3>\n  <p>• A Service Connection is a secure configuration that allows Azure Pipelines to connect to external services (e.g., Azure Subscription, Kubernetes Cluster, Docker Registry, GitHub, Jira) without exposing credentials in the pipeline code.</p>\n  <p>• How it works: It stores the authentication details (Service Principal, OAuth token, or Kubernetes kubeconfig) securely in Azure DevOps. Developers simply reference the service connection name in their YAML code.</p>\n  <p>• Best Practice: Restrict service connection access to specific pipelines and branches using security permissions.</p>\n</div>",
