    "id": 282,
    "category": "Terraform (IaC)",
    "question": "How can you manage multiple Azure subscriptions using a single Terraform workspace or project?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>🏗️ <strong>How can you manage multiple Azure subscriptions using a single Terraform workspace or project?</strong></h3>\n  <p>To manage resources across multiple Azure subscriptions in a single Terraform workspace:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Multiple Providers</strong>: Configure multiple provider blocks referencing distinct subscription IDs.</li>\n    <li><strong>Use Alias</strong>: Assign an <code>alias</code> attribute to secondary providers:</li>\n  <pre style=\"background:#111;padding:.6rem;border-radius:.4rem;\"><code class=\"language-hcl\">   provider \"azurerm\" {\n     alias           = \"billing_sub\"\n     subscription_id = \"xxxx-xxxx-xxxx\"\n     features {}\n   }</code></pre>\n    <li><strong>Explicit Call</strong>: Declare <code>provider = azurerm.billing_sub</code> in resources targeting the second subscription.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
