    "question": "How do you integrate Terraform deployments with Azure DevOps pipelines?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>🏗️ <strong>How do you integrate Terraform deployments with Azure DevOps pipelines?</strong></h3>\n  <p>To integrate Terraform with Azure DevOps YAML pipelines:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Define Service Connection</strong>: Configure an Azure Resource Manager service connection using Workload Identity Federation (OIDC).</li>\n    <li><strong>Pipeline YAML Tasks</strong>: Use the official Terraform CLI tasks in your pipeline:</li>\n  <pre style=\"background:#111;padding:.6rem;border-radius:.4rem;\"><code class=\"language-yaml\">   - task: TerraformTaskV4@4\n     inputs:\n       provider: 'azurerm'\n       command: 'init'\n       backendServiceArm: 'my-service-connection'\n       backendAzureRmStorageAccountName: 'prodstates'\n   - task: TerraformTaskV4@4\n     inputs:\n       command: 'apply'\n       environmentServiceNameAzureRM: 'my-service-connection'</code></pre>\n    <li><strong>Quality checks</strong>: Add validation tools like <code>tfsec</code> or <code>checkov</code> before the deployment steps.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
