    "id": 284,
    "category": "Terraform (IaC)",
    "question": "What strategies can you use to prevent accidental deletion or recreation of critical Azure resources in Terraform?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>🏗️ <strong>What strategies can you use to prevent accidental deletion or recreation of critical Azure resources in Terraform?</strong></h3>\n  <p>To protect critical cloud resources from accidental deletion in Terraform:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Lifecycle Meta-Argument</strong>: Add <code>prevent_destroy = true</code> inside the resource <code>lifecycle</code> block. Any <code>terraform destroy</code> attempt will error out immediately.</li>\n    <li><strong>Azure Resource Locks</strong>: Provision an <code>azurerm_management_lock</code> resource in HCL with the lock level set to <code>CanNotDelete</code>:</li>\n  <pre style=\"background:#111;padding:.6rem;border-radius:.4rem;\"><code class=\"language-hcl\">   resource \"azurerm_management_lock\" \"lock\" {\n     name       = \"prevent-delete\"\n     scope      = azurerm_resource_group.rg.id\n     lock_level = \"CanNotDelete\"\n   }</code></pre>\n    <li><strong>RBAC Permissions</strong>: Restrict delete permissions on production subscriptions.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
    "difficulty": "Medium",
    "source": "Professional Interview QA Guide",
    "company": null
