    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>🏗️ <strong>How would you create an Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS) cluster with Terraform and manage its node pools?</strong></h3>\n  <p>Kubernetes Services expose pods to network traffic using stable IPs:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>ClusterIP</strong>: Exposes the service internally within the cluster (default).</li>\n    <li><strong>NodePort</strong>: Opens a static port on each node's IP to expose the service externally.</li>\n    <li><strong>LoadBalancer</strong>: Provisions a cloud public load balancer to route external traffic directly to nodes.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
