    "id": 315,
    "category": "DevOps General",
    "question": "What is Deployment approval and gate approvals ?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>💡 <strong>What is Deployment approval and gate approvals ?</strong></h3>\n  <p>Implementing deployment approvals and release gates in Azure DevOps:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Manual Approvals</strong>: Pauses the pipeline stage and notifies reviewers. Deployment only continues once approved.</li>\n    <li><strong>Release Gates</strong>: Automated checks that evaluate criteria (e.g., query Azure Monitor alerts, call REST APIs, check active incidents) before allowing the deployment to proceed to the next stage (e.g. Production).</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
