    "category": "DevOps General",
    "question": "Regular expression – for redirection tolls ?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>💡 <strong>Regular expression – for redirection tolls ?</strong></h3>\n  <p>Regular Expressions (Regex) are used in web server redirection rules (like Nginx location blocks or IIS rewrite rules):</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Example</strong>: Redirect all HTTP requests from <code>/old-path/(.*)</code> to <code>/new-path/$1</code>.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h4>🔹 Nginx location configuration</h4>\n  <p>`location ~* ^/old-path/(.*) {</p>\n  <p>return 301 /new-path/$1;</p>\n  <p>}`</p>\n</div>",
