    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>☸️ <strong>EKS Cluster ?</strong></h3>\n  <p>AWS Elastic Kubernetes Service (EKS) is Amazon's managed Kubernetes service:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Control Plane</strong>: AWS automatically manages control plane nodes, etcd, upgrades, and high availability.</li>\n    <li><strong>Worker Nodes</strong>: Deployed in your AWS account using EC2 Auto Scaling groups (Managed Node Groups) or AWS Fargate (serverless containers). Standard <code>kubectl</code> commands are used to manage workloads.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
