    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>☁️ <strong>What is VNET pairing ?</strong></h3>\n  <p>VNET Peering securely connects two Azure Virtual Networks (VNETs):</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Private Routing</strong>: Communication flows over Microsoft's private global backbone using private IP addresses. Traffic never goes over the public internet.</li>\n    <li><strong>Setup</strong>: Requires configuring two uni-directional peering links (VNET-A to VNET-B, and VNET-B to VNET-A) with Gateway Transit options for shared resources.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
