    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>💻 <strong>How to upgrade the OS Patch, tell command for ubuntu and RedHat?</strong></h3>\n  <p>To upgrade the OS patches on Linux servers:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Ubuntu/Debian</strong>: Run <code>sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y</code> to refresh the package lists and download/install the security patches.</li>\n    <li><strong>RedHat/CentOS</strong>: Run <code>sudo yum update -y</code> or <code>sudo dnf upgrade -y</code> to update the operating system packages.</li>\n    <li><strong>Production coordination</strong>: In enterprise environments, VMs are patched sequentially, and reboots are coordinated through maintenance windows or automated tooling like Azure Update Manager.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
