    "question": "What is Traffic Manager?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>💡 <strong>What is Traffic Manager?</strong></h3>\n  <p>Azure Traffic Manager is a DNS-based traffic load balancer:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Routing</strong>: Directs client requests to global endpoints (e.g., Web apps in East US and West Europe) based on routing methods like performance, latency, or priority.</li>\n    <li><strong>Health Probes</strong>: Continuously monitors endpoints. If one region goes offline, Traffic Manager automatically redirects DNS queries to healthy regions.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
