    "question": "What is ClusterIp?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>☸️ <strong>What is ClusterIp?</strong></h3>\n  <p>A <strong>ClusterIP</strong> is the default service type in Kubernetes:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Behavior</strong>: It exposes the service on an internal IP address within the cluster. It makes the service only accessible from within the cluster, allowing internal pods to communicate.</li>\n    <li><strong>Use Case</strong>: Ideal for backend microservices, databases, and caching layers that do not need to be exposed to external traffic.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
