    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>💡 <strong>What is pakage manager in ubuntu and Redhat?</strong></h3>\n  <p>Package managers automate installing, updating, and removing software packages:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Ubuntu/Debian</strong>: Uses <code>apt</code> (Advanced Package Tool) to download and install <code>.deb</code> files: <code>sudo apt update && sudo apt install <package></code>.</li>\n    <li><strong>RedHat/CentOS/Fedora</strong>: Uses <code>dnf</code> or <code>yum</code> to manage <code>.rpm</code> files: <code>sudo dnf install <package></code>.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
