    "id": 354,
    "category": "Company Wise QA",
    "question": "Q. How we run kubernetes and maintain container",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>☸️ <strong>Q. How we run kubernetes and maintain container</strong></h3>\n  <p>Running Kubernetes workloads and maintaining container health:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Probes</strong>: Define Liveness probes (restarts container if app locks up) and Readiness probes (stops routing network traffic if app is loading).</li>\n    <li><strong>Deployments</strong>: Use RollingUpdates to apply container image updates without downtime. Set resources (Limits/Requests) to prevent pod Out-Of-Memory (OOM) eviction.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
