    "id": 360,
    "category": "Company Wise QA",
    "question": "How do you connect your VM with private IP?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>💡 <strong>How do you connect your VM with private IP?</strong></h3>\n  <p>To connect to an Azure VM securely using its private IP address:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Azure Bastion</strong>: Configure Bastion in the VNET. It provides secure browser-based RDP/SSH tunnel sessions without public IPs.</li>\n    <li><strong>VPN Gateway / ExpressRoute</strong>: Set up a Point-to-Site or Site-to-Site VPN linking local machines directly to the Azure VNET.</li>\n    <li><strong>Jumpbox VM</strong>: Create a jump VM with a public IP, connect via SSH, and SSH into the target private VM from there.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
