    "category": "Company Wise QA",
    "question": "If vendor pushes a patch while developer is working on a VM ,how will you handle this delta patching?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>💡 <strong>If vendor pushes a patch while developer is working on a VM ,how will you handle this delta patching?</strong></h3>\n  <p>To handle delta patching when updates are pushed during active development:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Maintenance Windows</strong>: Configure update policies to apply patches only during designated maintenance windows (e.g., weekends/night shifts).</li>\n    <li><strong>Stage Validation</strong>: Apply delta patches to staging/dev copies of the VM first. Run validation tests before letting the patch install on the active development server.</li>\n    <li><strong>Backup snapshot</strong>: Take an Azure Disk snapshot before applying patches so you can quickly roll back if the patch breaks active configurations.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
