    "question": "How do you access the state file from your local machine cli ?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>🏗️ <strong>How do you access the state file from your local machine cli ?</strong></h3>\n  <p>To access the state file from your local machine CLI:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Configure Backend</strong>: Ensure the backend block in HCL points to the remote storage (e.g. Azure Blob container).</li>\n    <li><strong>Terraform CLI</strong>: Run <code>terraform init</code> to authorize connections, and use <code>terraform state list</code> or <code>terraform state show <resource_address></code> to inspect state parameters.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
