    "question": "How to create certificate?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>💡 <strong>How to create certificate?</strong></h3>\n  <p>To create and configure SSL/TLS certificates for web servers:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Self-Signed (Testing)</strong>: Generate a certificate locally using OpenSSL: <code>openssl req -x509 -newkey rsa:4096 -keyout domain.key -out domain.crt -days 365 -nodes</code>.</li>\n    <li><strong>CA-Signed (Production)</strong>: Generate a CSR (Certificate Signing Request), submit it to a trusted Certificate Authority (like Let's Encrypt using automated Certbot clients, or DigiCert), download the validated certificate, and install it.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
