    "id": 422,
    "category": "Docker & Kubernetes",
    "question": "How to troubleshoot docker container?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>🐳 <strong>How to troubleshoot docker container?</strong></h3>\n  <p>Step-by-step process to troubleshoot failing Docker containers:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Inspect logs</strong>: Run <code>docker logs <container-id></code> to check application standard outputs and error stack traces.</li>\n    <li><strong>Check container state</strong>: Run <code>docker inspect <container-id></code> to check network ports, environment variables, and mount states.</li>\n    <li><strong>Live Shell access</strong>: Execute a terminal session inside the running container: <code>docker exec -it <container-id> /bin/bash</code> or <code>sh</code> to inspect internal files and connection ports.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
