    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>☁️ <strong>If you have to migrate a Apache bassed system to azure, what would be your step?</strong></h3>\n  <p>Steps to migrate an Apache-based web application to Azure:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Lift-and-Shift</strong>: Create an Azure VM, install Apache, copy configurations (<code>httpd.conf</code>), and migrate application files.</li>\n    <li><strong>Refactor to Containers (Best Practice)</strong>: Containerize the Apache workload and deploy to Azure App Service or Container Apps to eliminate OS-level maintenance.</li>\n    <li><strong>DNS Cutover</strong>: Update your external DNS records to point to the new Azure endpoint.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
