    "category": "Company Wise QA",
    "question": "What are security measoures available in Azure?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>☁️ <strong>What are security measoures available in Azure?</strong></h3>\n  <p>Key security layers available in Microsoft Azure:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Identity</strong>: Microsoft Entra ID (formerly Azure AD), MFA, conditional access policies, and Role-Based Access Control (RBAC).</li>\n    <li><strong>Network</strong>: Network Security Groups (NSGs), Azure Bastion, Private Endpoints, Azure Firewall, and WAF.</li>\n    <li><strong>Data</strong>: Azure Key Vault for secrets management, and Storage Encryption at Rest.</li>\n    <li><strong>Governance</strong>: Azure Policy for compliance and Defender for Cloud.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
    "source": "Professional Interview QA Guide",
    "company": "BEE Solver Tech"
