    "id": 433,
    "category": "Company Wise QA",
    "question": "How to access server using authentication key apart from username and password?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>🔐 <strong>How to access server using authentication key apart from username and password?</strong></h3>\n  <p>Accessing Linux servers securely using SSH keys:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Key Generation</strong>: Generate an SSH keypair on your local machine using <code>ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096</code>.</li>\n    <li><strong>Distribute Key</strong>: Copy the public key to the remote server using <code>ssh-copy-id user@host</code> (which writes it to <code>~/.ssh/authorized_keys</code>).</li>\n    <li><strong>Connect</strong>: SSH using the private key: <code>ssh -i path_to_private_key user@host</code> and disable password authentication.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
    "source": "Professional Interview QA Guide",
    "company": "BEE Solver Tech"
