    "question": "If you have created resources manually through the portal, how can you store them in a Terraform state file?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>🏗️ <strong>If you have created resources manually through the portal, how can you store them in a Terraform state file?</strong></h3>\n  <p>To import manually created Azure resources into Terraform:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>HCL Block</strong>: Write the empty resource block in your HCL configuration: <code>resource \"azurerm_storage_account\" \"sa\" {}</code>.</li>\n    <li><strong>Import command</strong>: Run the import command: <code>terraform import azurerm_storage_account.sa /subscriptions/.../resourceGroups/...</code>.</li>\n    <li><strong>Reconcile</strong>: Run <code>terraform plan</code> and update your HCL block parameters to match the properties shown in the plan output.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
