    "id": 446,
    "category": "Company Wise QA",
    "question": "What is the architecture of the meta-argument in Terraform?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>🏗️ <strong>What is the architecture of the meta-argument in Terraform?</strong></h3>\n  <p>Meta-arguments in Terraform are configuration parameters that modify how resources are created:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>count</strong>: Creates a specified number of resources: <code>count = 3</code>.</li>\n    <li><strong>for_each</strong>: Iterates over maps/sets, creating resources dynamically based on keys.</li>\n    <li><strong>depends_on</strong>: Declares explicit deployment dependencies.</li>\n    <li><strong>lifecycle</strong>: Configures lifecycle behavior (e.g., <code>prevent_destroy</code>).</li>\n    <li><strong>provider</strong>: Specifies provider aliases.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
    "difficulty": "Easy",
