    "question": "You created an Azure Key Vault. what type of access will see in rbac ?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>☁️ <strong>You created an Azure Key Vault. what type of access will see in rbac ?</strong></h3>\n  <p>Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) is the authorization system in Azure:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Core Concept</strong>: Restricts access to resources based on assigned roles. It answers 'Who (Security Principal) can do What (Role definition) to Which resource (Scope)'.</li>\n    <li><strong>Built-in Roles</strong>: Owner (full access + delegate access), Contributor (full access except delegate), and Reader (view access only).</li>\n    <li><strong>Best Practice</strong>: Apply the principle of least privilege, assigning roles at the resource group or resource scope rather than the subscription level.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
