    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>🏗️ <strong>How do you enable debugging in Terraform? To enable debugging in Terraform, you can set specific environment variables that control the logging level and output location.Terraform uses the TF_LOG environment variable to control logging verbosity.</strong></h3>\n  <p>Production implementation guide for: <strong>Enable Debugging In Terraform To Enable Debugging In Terraform, You Can Set Specific Environment Variables That Control The Logging Level And Output Location.Terraform Uses The Tf_Log Environment Variable To Control Logging Verbosity.</strong> in Terraform Infrastructure as Code (IaC):</p>\n  <h4>🔹 Prerequisites & Credentials</h4>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li>Configure target permissions using cloud Service Principals, Managed Identities, or OIDC pipeline logins.</li>\n    <li>Install correct local utility versions (e.g. Terraform CLI, Ansible Core, or Kubernetes kubectl).</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h4>🔹 Configuration Steps</h4>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li>Write the declarative manifest file (e.g., <code>main.tf</code> HCL files, Kubernetes YAML deployment cards, or Ansible playbook files).</li>\n    <li>Enforce lint checks and run plan evaluations (e.g., <code>terraform plan</code> or <code>kubectl apply --dry-run=client</code>) to test validation.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <h4>🔹 Deployment & Troubleshooting</h4>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li>Apply updates to a designated staging environment. Review application health logs (<code>kubectl logs</code> or <code>/var/log</code>).</li>\n    <li>Promote resources to production using release environments locked by review approvals and automated monitor gates.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
