    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>🔀 <strong>14.⁠ ⁠What is the difference between a push and a commit in version control systems?</strong></h3>\n  <p>Version control tracks and manages changes to software code over time:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>Benefits</strong>: Enables multi-developer collaboration, code reviews, audit history, and easy rollbacks of faulty code.</li>\n    <li><strong>Git</strong>: The industry standard distributed version control tool.</li>\n    <li><strong>Platforms</strong>: Remote platforms like GitHub, GitLab, and Azure Repos provide hosting, pull request workflows, and pipeline integrations.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
