    "question": "When integrating Snowflake with Azure DevOps to trigger a pipeline, which authentication method should you use?",
    "answer": "<div class=\"answer-rich\">\n  <h3>☁️ <strong>When integrating Snowflake with Azure DevOps to trigger a pipeline, which authentication method should you use?</strong></h3>\n  <p>Pipeline triggers automate the execution of build and release pipelines:</p>\n  <ul style=\"margin-left:1.2rem;\">\n    <li><strong>CI Trigger</strong>: Starts a pipeline run automatically when code is pushed to specific branches (e.g. <code>main</code>, <code>develop</code>).</li>\n    <li><strong>PR Trigger</strong>: Runs build tests when a Pull Request is opened to validate code merging.</li>\n    <li><strong>Scheduled Trigger</strong>: Runs on a recurring time window (cron style) for daily test runs.</li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
